task_description: Facing the building to your North-East (approx. 33°), estimate the height of the main building in front of you in meters. Answer with one number and a short rationale.

reason: The current pitch of 0° may not capture the full height of the building; rotating upward will reveal the roofline needed for accurate height estimation.
The current heading (0°N) is misaligned with the target building at 33°NE; rotating right by 33° will center the building in view while maintaining the upward pitch to capture its full height.

The current pitch of 0° does not capture the building's roof; rotating upward to 30° pitch will reveal the full vertical extent needed for height estimation while maintaining alignment with the 33°NE target building.
